cards.desc:
**Create an application that allows T4J to manage payment made by organizations to freelancers.**
The main objectives of the project are to create an application that allows users to:
Create Payment Transactions
Create Tasks
Create Freelancers
Load Historical Transactions from File
Define Time and Day of the Month Unpayed Tasks Will Be Payed
Automatically Make Payments
Visualize Overall Statistics About Task Execution Times
Add New Organizations
Send E-mail to Late Freelancers
Serialize Information To File

cards.desc:
During the client meeting of 01/06/2020 the client specified the following:

- We can assume (up until and including the design of the design phase) that we will show all the statistics at the same time, the UI handles weather to show them separately.
- IDs are not automatic except for the freelancer's.
- The freelancer's ID is the the first letters of their first and last name followed by a number that starts at 1 and increments when the ID enters in conflit.
- The freelancer's ID can be loaded from file.
- An organization has a name and NIF.
- UC5's frequency is normally once a year but can be changed anytime.
- We don't have to use any of the provided code.
- The freelancer's IBAN and e-email is unique.
- A collaborator or manager don't belong to more than one organization.
- Passwords that are generated are 7 characters long and made up of alphanumeric characters.
- Anytime information is available on the system it should be selectable, otherwise it should be able to introduce it.
- The data available about statistics is about the population, the data in the system is a sample
- When introducing data there *can* be a loop.
- The TXT file that has the transactions has the flowing information the account where the money was transferred the task (description and ID) and monetary value (in EUR and the freelancer's native currency) the freelancer's ID.
- Objects cannot be updated.
- Payments are always made automatically.
- Payments are always automatic.
- The ordering of the freelancers by payment or name is done in the UI.
- A collaborator/manager can only visualize statistics about their own organization, the administrator can visualize statistics about everyone.
cards.name: Client Answers 01/06/2020

cards.desc:
During the client meeting of 01/06/2020 the client specified the following:

- Only the classes in the **model** need to be tested.
- Historical transactions are not yet payed.
- The diference between *txt* and *csv* files is that *txt* files are separated by **tabs**, *csv* files are separated by **comas**.
- The value that will be payed needs to be shown before the transaction is saved.
- If there is duplicate data in the file, the system should keep loading the unique data, the system *can* show the user the lines where there was an error.
- For the statistics in **UC9** the sample size needs to be taken into account.
- The API to convert between currencies should, at least, convert euros to:
    - Dollar (USA)
    - Libra (UK)
    - Real (Brazil)
    - Yen (Japan)
    - Yuan (China)
